221
00:11:26,959 --> 00:11:28,958
{\an8}let me put you
out of your misery.

222
00:11:28,959 --> 00:11:31,916
{\an8}Actually, I don't think
you hit it.

223
00:11:31,917 --> 00:11:34,165
{\an8}No, he's suffering--
pure agony.

224
00:11:34,166 --> 00:11:36,165
{\an8}Oh, my God!
Stop!

225
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:38,416
What, are you crazy?

226
00:11:38,417 --> 00:11:40,875
Crazy with compassion.
Come on. Watch me
blow its head off.

227
00:11:44,834 --> 00:11:47,417
Die! Die!
So that you may know peace.

228
00:11:57,250 --> 00:12:00,000
Truck!

229
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:06,625
Stop the car,
you psychopath!

230
00:12:22,959 --> 00:12:24,958
Oh, God!

231
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:30,750
Raccoon!

232
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:35,624
No, I'm never coming home.

233
00:12:35,625 --> 00:12:37,750
Because you're
smothering me, Linda.

234
00:12:42,208 --> 00:12:45,624
I was wrong.
I'll be home by 9:00.

235
00:12:45,625 --> 00:12:49,500
Because I promised Derek
I'd meet him for a drink.
That's why 9:00!

236
00:12:58,417 --> 00:13:01,000
And let the love
come flowing back.

237
00:13:04,083 --> 00:13:06,125
Stay away from me!

238
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:16,207
<i>♪ I'm all right ♪</i>

239
00:13:16,208 --> 00:13:18,792
<i>♪ Nobody worry about me ♪</i>

240
00:13:20,083 --> 00:13:22,624
This is great.
By the way,

241
00:13:22,625 --> 00:13:25,082
great call on this
Rasta disguise, Steve.

242
00:13:25,083 --> 00:13:27,124
I'm "ganja" wear it
all the time.

243
00:13:29,125 --> 00:13:31,124
Hey, Steve,
is this your friend?

244
00:13:31,125 --> 00:13:33,124
Yeah. Lindsay,
this is Roger.

245
00:13:33,125 --> 00:13:35,040
- Nice to meet you.
- Charmed.

246
00:13:35,041 --> 00:13:38,332
- And this is Jewel.
- Your date.

247
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:40,624
Oh, God. Oh, God.
I'm out. I'm out.
Ew! Ew!

248
00:13:40,625 --> 00:13:42,374
Hey, we had a deal.

249
00:13:42,375 --> 00:13:46,666
Steve, she's so ugly.

250
00:13:46,667 --> 00:13:49,833
So ugly.

251
00:13:49,834 --> 00:13:52,457
Too bad.
I snuck you out
so you could be my wingman.

252
00:13:52,458 --> 00:13:54,457
Now you can make nice
with Jewel,

253
00:13:54,458 --> 00:13:57,499
- or you can go home
and rot in the attic.
- Uh, Steve,

254
00:13:57,500 --> 00:14:00,541
"Jamaican" me crazy.

255
00:14:00,542 --> 00:14:04,165
Sorry. I've had that one
loaded up all night.

256
00:14:04,166 --> 00:14:06,833
Ahh. This picture
was taken on our honeymoon.

257
00:14:06,834 --> 00:14:10,499
It's the only photo of Francine
where you can't see Vaj.

258
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:14,708
Ah, Vaj--
the little island boy
who served as our tour guide.

259
00:14:14,709 --> 00:14:18,999
I see from her wristband
that you were at a Sandals
all-inclusive resort.

260
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,958
Hmm! Fancy.

261
00:14:20,959 --> 00:14:22,624
Wait a minute.

262
00:14:22,625 --> 00:14:25,166
I know just the thing
to trigger her memory.

263
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:41,207
Hayley, I thought
we were going to--
<i>♪ Burning Man ♪</i>

264
00:14:41,208 --> 00:14:44,124
Sorry, but my mom decided
to throw a rager.

265
00:14:44,125 --> 00:14:46,667
Besides, Jeff,
I never said I was going.

266
00:14:47,834 --> 00:14:51,041
Party foul! Consume!

267
00:14:53,208 --> 00:14:56,541
I had this boyfriend.
He was in an avalanche.

268
00:14:56,542 --> 00:14:58,999
He survived three days
on melted snow,

269
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,165
and his grandfather
found him

270
00:15:01,166 --> 00:15:04,958
because he had a dream
about the exact spot
where he was trapped.

271
00:15:04,959 --> 00:15:08,249
Wow!
You had a boyfriend?

272
00:15:08,250 --> 00:15:11,666
Oh, you have--
You have a little thing.

273
00:15:11,667 --> 00:15:13,666
Oh, Roger, stop it.

274
00:15:13,667 --> 00:15:17,249
- I don't have a hard time
looking at you.
- At me?

275
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:19,499
I can see past
your hydrocephalic head

276
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:21,666
and into your beautiful mind.

277
00:15:21,667 --> 00:15:23,958
You're like Russell Crowe,
and I'm Jennifer Connelly.

278
00:15:23,959 --> 00:15:26,083
Yeah. Yeah, you're
Jennifer Connelly.

279
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:30,874
Uncomfortable.

280
00:15:30,875 --> 00:15:32,916
Get a room, you two.

281
00:15:32,917 --> 00:15:35,040
Maybe we should lead
by example.

282
00:15:35,041 --> 00:15:37,541
Or we could just
go back to your place
and make out.

283
00:15:37,542 --> 00:15:40,040
Yeah, okay,
I understand.

284
00:15:40,041 --> 00:15:43,166
Well, I had
a fun time anyway.
See you at school.

285
00:15:45,834 --> 00:15:47,082
Huh?

286
00:15:47,083 --> 00:15:48,582
Okay!

287
00:15:51,375 --> 00:15:54,249
- Hayley, where's your mother?
- Last time I saw her,
she was in the kitchen,

288
00:15:54,250 --> 00:15:56,708
- serving up body shots.
- What a hostess.

289
00:15:56,709 --> 00:16:00,332
- She's not here.
- There's a note in frosting
on the fridge.

290
00:16:00,333 --> 00:16:02,499
"Hayley-- Me and Jeff
went to Burning Man
together.

291
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:04,499
Rock on,
Francine."

292
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,916
My mother stole
my boyfriend!

293
00:16:06,917 --> 00:16:08,916
Your boyfriend
stole my wife!

294
00:16:08,917 --> 00:16:10,916
Let's get back at them
by dating each other.

295
00:16:10,917 --> 00:16:14,500
Wait a minute.
Daddy didn't think that through.

296
00:16:19,667 --> 00:16:22,499
The sandman's starting
to goose me.

297
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:25,040
Here. Have some coffee.

298
00:16:25,041 --> 00:16:27,040
- Klaus!
- When you come home <i>und</i> pack,

299
00:16:27,041 --> 00:16:29,833
I heard you and Hayley
talking about this Burning Man,

300
00:16:29,834 --> 00:16:32,290
so I says to <i>mein</i> self,
"Road trip!"

301
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:35,208
Stan, by the way,
I could not hold <i>mein</i> pee-pee.

302
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:39,833
Honestly,

303
00:16:39,834 --> 00:16:41,916
I only
went out with you
to get Jewel a date,

304
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:44,332
- but you're a lot less
of a dork than I thought.
- Stick around.

305
00:16:44,333 --> 00:16:47,499
I think you'll find
I'm a lot less
of everything.

306
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:50,916
You can do
whatever you want to me.

307
00:16:50,917 --> 00:16:54,666
Oh, so I can crate you
and hide you in that warehouse
at the end of <i>Raiders?</i>

308
00:16:54,667 --> 00:16:58,249
So funny.
Kiss me, funny boy.

309
00:16:58,250 --> 00:17:01,666
I know, I know.
Bad for the ozone.

310
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:07,165
Yeah, Burning Man
is great this year.

311
00:17:07,166 --> 00:17:10,791
Ow! Ow!

312
00:17:10,792 --> 00:17:12,791
{\an8}Dad, we've been searching
all night.

313
00:17:12,792 --> 00:17:14,541
{\an8}Let's just start fresh
in the morning.

314
00:17:14,542 --> 00:17:16,791
{\an8}Francine? Francine?

315
00:17:16,792 --> 00:17:18,791
{\an8}I'm not just
saying this
to be clever--

316
00:17:18,792 --> 00:17:20,959
{\an8}I really feel
like a fish
out of water here.

317
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:26,040
What's the deal
with the flower?

318
00:17:26,041 --> 00:17:28,916
On our wedding day,
I placed this yellow flower
in your mom's white bouquet.

319
00:17:28,917 --> 00:17:32,708
It symbolized
her sunshine brightening
my otherwise cloudy world.

320
00:17:32,709 --> 00:17:35,916
Dad, I've never seen
this side of you.
It's so sweet.

321
00:17:35,917 --> 00:17:38,082
Well, if you tell anybody
I'll kill you.

322
00:17:40,083 --> 00:17:41,916
Ah. I'm serious.
I will kill you.

323
00:17:41,917 --> 00:17:44,165
I will reach into your chest,
pull out your beating heart,

324
00:17:44,166 --> 00:17:46,708
and eat it--
all of it, every last bit.

325
00:17:46,709 --> 00:17:49,249
Well, sweet dreams, angel.

326
00:17:49,250 --> 00:17:51,249
I-I-It's not you.
It's the timing,
you know?

327
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:53,207
I just got out
of a bad relationship.

328
00:17:53,208 --> 00:17:55,874
You're lying.
I'm a loser.

329
00:17:55,875 --> 00:17:58,499
Don't be like that.
You're not a loser.

330
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:01,082
Think how pretty you make
people look by contrast.

331
00:18:01,083 --> 00:18:03,082
That's a gift.

332
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:05,250
Gotcha!

333
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:09,249
Oh, my God!
You're an alien!

334
00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:11,958
Oh, my God!
Lindsay! Lindsay!

335
00:18:11,959 --> 00:18:14,457
Roger is an ali--

336
00:18:14,458 --> 00:18:16,666
- Roger!
- She was all over me,
and my wig fell off,

337
00:18:16,667 --> 00:18:18,875
and we'd be in big trouble.

338
00:18:20,125 --> 00:18:22,249
Did you see
where they went?

339
00:18:22,250 --> 00:18:25,083
- Who?
- The black guys who did this.

340
00:18:28,667 --> 00:18:31,624
Aah! Mr. Smith!

341
00:18:31,625 --> 00:18:33,999
- Where's my wife?
- She ditched me
as soon as we got here.

342
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,416
I just ran away with her
to get a rise out of Hayley.

343
00:18:36,417 --> 00:18:39,082
- Please don't kill me!
Let me get this straight.

344
00:18:39,083 --> 00:18:42,541
You ran away with my
memory-erased mother
to a pagan festival

345
00:18:42,542 --> 00:18:44,916
- just to get my attention?
- Did it work?

346
00:18:44,917 --> 00:18:47,666
Did it ever!
Mmm!

347
00:18:49,834 --> 00:18:53,457
You know, we're
about to go on tour
to Bangkok and Amsterdam,

348
00:18:53,458 --> 00:18:55,582
and this hot piece
of mama's comin' with us.

349
00:18:55,583 --> 00:18:59,416
I am ripped off my ass!

350
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,541
Francine!

351
00:19:03,542 --> 00:19:05,499
- You again?
- Look what I have.

352
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:08,333
Remember. Please remember.

353
00:19:09,875 --> 00:19:11,958
How long till it kicks in?

354
00:19:11,959 --> 00:19:14,374
Oh, Francine, for God's sake,
we're married.
You love me.

355
00:19:14,375 --> 00:19:18,958
Look, you're a stiff.
I could never fall in love
with a suit like you.

356
00:19:18,959 --> 00:19:21,834
A suit like me?
Well then,
I'll get rid of the suit.

357
00:19:24,125 --> 00:19:26,541
Huh? Huh?
Look at me.
Nothing stiff here.

358
00:19:26,542 --> 00:19:30,125
Hey, it's never gonna
happen with us.
Never!

359
00:19:33,417 --> 00:19:36,833
Because hang-gliding
makes me feel alive,
Linda, okay?

360
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:45,333
Francine!

361
00:19:54,625 --> 00:19:56,999
Don't worry. I'm leaving.

362
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,791
I just wanted you to be safe.

363
00:19:59,792 --> 00:20:03,582
You're the best thing
that ever happened to me,
and I took it for granted.

364
00:20:03,583 --> 00:20:05,791
I'm just happy that--

365
00:20:05,792 --> 00:20:09,374
Uh, that I got the privilege
to be with you
for the time that I did.

366
00:20:11,083 --> 00:20:13,749
Okay, my shoes are full.
I better go now.

367
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:18,709
I love you, Francine.
It's a little late,
but happy anniversary.

368
00:20:23,041 --> 00:20:25,166
Remember.

369
00:20:28,166 --> 00:20:30,499
- Stan?
- Francine?

370
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:32,874
Stan, it was so weird.

371
00:20:32,875 --> 00:20:35,916
And I was alone
and confused.

372
00:20:35,917 --> 00:20:39,499
And there was this raccoon,
and I knew who I was again.

373
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:41,499
Oh, Francine, thank God.

374
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:44,999
- I love you.
- I love you too, Stan.

375
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,834
That was gross.
I still love you.

376
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:54,958
Thanks for looking after me.
I'm so embarrassed.

377
00:20:54,959 --> 00:20:58,333
Don't be.
You were fun.
In fact, you were cool.

378
00:20:59,834 --> 00:21:02,458
Oh. Hey, funny story.

379
00:21:03,792 --> 00:21:05,499
A little bit longer,

380
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:07,416
and their last 24 hours
will be completely forgotten.

381
00:21:07,417 --> 00:21:09,833
- Oh, thank God.
- You are not
off the hook, mister.

382
00:21:09,834 --> 00:21:11,874
I am deeply
disappointed in you.

383
00:21:11,875 --> 00:21:15,125
- Dad, I was with this one.
- Oh. Well, outstanding.

384
00:21:53,667 --> 00:21:55,625
{\an8}Bye! Have a beautiful time.

